social_posts.post_text: Number 35 hit the ground today. This one should have been 36, but alas, Buck fever strikes again! #deerhunting #firstdeer #crossbowhunting
Did it from the ground tonight! #firstdeer #deerseason This one actually busted us but the next one got smoked.

We hunted from the ground without a blind tonight and had some awesome action on public land! This old doe was onto us but this hunter handled it perfectly by staying frozen and then acting quickly when she walked behind a tree to get set for her shot. These deer have been harassed by bow hunters since September and disturbed by pheasant hunters for a month, but that doesn’t mean they can’t be hunted successfully if you do it right. That’s number 36 for me this season. 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#firstdeer #girlhunter #deerhunting #huntingguide #crossbowhunting

What a morning! Got away from the crowds and hunted public bow only territory. We harvested a buck in the first thirty minutes, then had ten or twelve deer chasing and browsing in circles just out of range for an hour before we finally got the chance to make the double. We’ve harvested four deer in three days on five opportunities and I just can’t believe how well this season is going! These make it 38. 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#learntohunt #learntohuntnyc #deerseason #njdeerhunting #huntingguide

It’s buck week! Or so they call it here. I always find this to be my least successful week of the year because everyone and their brother goes hunting and drives push the deer into lockdown. This year I am bucking the trend! Always fun to break out the Savage after all the bow hunting. The 220 is my workhorse in gun season and I recommended it highly before I ever became a #savageambassador. This is number 39 for me and my clients this season. 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#wearesavage #savage220

It’s so hard to put people on deer once gun season is open! I’m proud of this one. We hunted near the top of a mountain really close to a bed I discovered in the snow last year and caught them coming down just before dark. That makes the tally 40!! 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#savageambassador #savagearms #wearesavage #savage220 #firstdeer #plusonemovement #learntohunt #learntohuntnyc

We didn’t have a lot of success with the public pheasants this year, but we had some good times for sure. His first season is in the books and he’s going to be a heck of a bird dog by next fall! #savageambassador #wearesavage
Should’ve been a four man limit but I’m not gonna name names. 😉 good times this morning putting some guys on their first geese! #savageambassador #savagearms #wearesavage
Another happy hunter tonight with his first deer. I thought we were going to be skunked but she came in right at the buzzer. That’s number 41 for the season.

It just. keeps. happening. I don’t know what to say! This deer season is unbelievable. One more hunt tomorrow and then it’s time for my Christmas break! This was someone’s first buck and is 42 for me. 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#firstbuck #deerseason #crossbowhunting #plusonemovement @missioncrossbows

It’s amazing how much food a flock of grackles can eat! I thought I had a herd of deer at this spot because 100 lbs of corn disappeared in 2 days. Turns out it was two deer (one now at the butcher) and an army of grackles! There was about 25 lbs on the ground this morning and after lunch it’s all gone. #grackle

This fox was helping himself to our gut pile from yesterday’s deer all day today. In the afternoon he started carrying chunks around and burying them for later. This chunk got hidden only 25 yards from the stand. Pretty fun to watch.
Got to treat @snugthejoiner_aws to a preserve hunt with my big brother and nephew today! Snug did pretty great for a 9.5 month old puppy. #savageambassador #savagearms #wearesavage

Had quite the adventure in the swamp this morning. Some birds were flying early but showed no interest in the decoys. Fog covering the river and high water didn’t help things. At 8am the pup was losing his patience so we went looking for birds on foot and instead of ducks we found a beautiful flush of winter oyster mushrooms! Back in the blind at 9am, I called in a group of geese and shamefully didn’t hit one. Later on we went scouting by boat and then foot again, sloshing through the flooded timber. We finally found a couple black ducks that flushed from a distance. It was clear that we weren’t sneaking up on anything in these conditions so I let @snugthejoiner_aws loose to run and he promptly flushed a previously crippled black duck from its hideout on the riverbank. I put the bird down and Snug finally made himself useful on a duck hunt! He’s been reluctant to enter the water before, but this time he found his courage after some crying and splashed in for the retrieve. Proud of him for that one. By most metrics it was a poor hunt but between the dog and the mushrooms it was a pretty special day. #duckhunting #savageambassador #savagearms #huntgathercook #wildfood #learntohuntnyc

It’s rare that I find mushrooms in January up here but it’s been quite warm lately and these winter varieties of oyster mushrooms are remarkably hardy. I love finding them! The best part is that there aren’t any bugs to eat them before I do. #foraging #njforaging #oystermushrooms

We don’t usually see this big of a deer on public land in January, but we’ll take it. I didn’t even know it was there until the client put one through his heart! I heard the shot and turned to see the deer standing still at 60 yards and thought it was a miss at first, haha. He didn’t make it any further. #learntohuntnyc #learntohunt #huntingguide

What a crazy encounter in the @weatherwool swamp yesterday! I took my puppy out for a walk since the ducks weren’t around and we came right up on a bedded buck that just sat there with us at 10 yards. I shared the video with the owner and a group of friends with permission to hunt, and sure enough one of them went in there and harvested him on their lunch break. Turned out his hind quarter on the opposite side was pretty roughed up. Looks like he got hit by a car or something. #deerhunting #deerseason #buck #duckhunting #hunting #learntohuntnyc

Best part of the day! We had to work for this one. They’re getting very wise and very careful out there. This is 44 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#learntohunt #learntohuntnyc #huntingguide #firstdeer
@weatherwool swamp does it again for someone’s first deer in the late season! 45 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌

We had a dramatic finish last night! After a long day of nothing, we heard this buck snorting from the ridge. Evidently the wind swirled on us. He spent 15 minutes pacing around in the thick stuff and even came within 15 yards of the blind without coming into the open. Finally he stepped out at 25 yards but immediately started walking away, and just when I thought it wasn’t going to happen…#girlbowhunter #firstbuck #learntohunt #deerhunting #huntingguide #learntohuntnyc

First buck with a bow. Right through the heart at 30 yards. That makes for a proud guide! #learntohunt #firstbuck #bowhunting #girlbowhunter #huntingguide #learntohuntnyc 
That’s number 46 this season. Can we make it to 50?! 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌

The deer surprised us with early movement yesterday. Luckily we were ready for it! Especially happy for this guy to get his first deer because he’s a chef and is gonna do all sorts of cool stuff with his meat. That’s 47 🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌🦌#learntohunt #learntohuntnyc #huntingguide #savageambassador #wearesavage #savage220 #huntingmentor #apprenticehunter #firstdeer

Finally made it on the water in Karachi! @mustafafarishta took me to French Beach and we did some snorkeling alongside a guide who was spear fishing for us. He caught a few fish and a couple lobsters and then we found some guys to cook them up for us. Good times!

I post a lot of success stories and sometimes that gives people the wrong impression about what it’s all about with this hunting stuff. This right here is it. Perfectly done venison backstrap is so good that it’s impossible to do justice to the experience of eating it with words.

This is Pakistani Keema Aloo with venison that I made this week. It’s not very photogenic but it’s a flavor bomb that will change your life! I filmed this dish with some foraged extras for @savagearms on @carbontvmedia and you can find the recipe on the Savage Blog if you want to try it. #wildfood #venison #savageambassador
I gave @snugthejoiner_aws the green light to pursue some geese this morning. It was a fun show. He gave it two tries but they easily outpaced him, haha.
These deer were just a block from our house and they provided the opportunity for us to do some steadiness training on @snugthejoiner_aws who has an intense deer to chase them. He did pretty well!

I never get tired of hearing my nephew react to the fact that he’s filming a wild Turkey that I was about turn into dinner. Can’t wait to get down south and do it again! #turkeyhunting #turkeyseason

What an incredible opener for us in Tennessee. It was one of those rare days when things go exactly how they should. The weather was perfect. We barely heard a gobble at first, and the only one was far away from the property, but soon there was a whole flock out in the field. They went out of sight behind a rise and after a while I suddenly heard a spit behind us. A few minutes later we spotted movement, and ultimately watched him breed a hen before coming close to bully the Jake decoy. We stuck around to try and get one for me, and later heard some distant gobbles, made a move, set up cautiously, and called in two big gobblers with just two or three yelps on a box call. Last we heard from them, they sounded like they were going away, but I stuck to my silence and they came straight in without making a sound. Days like this are so special. You can hear it in my voice at the end! #turkeyhunting #turkeyseason #savageambassador #wearesavage #savagerenegauge

Two days, four gobblers! My big brother and I tagged out in TN day two with a textbook double. I called these birds over from probably 400 yards away and they charged in and started attacking the Jake decoy. Didn’t get that on film because my nephew was filming and had to plug his ears, haha. Definitely a fan of the later start on the season down here. Usually the birds are uncooperative and stick to their harems in the past but with the hens starting to nest they have been eager to investigate calling. #turkeyseason #savageambassador #wearesavage #reneguage
In case you were wondering: deer are freaked out by turkey decoys 🤣 #turkeyhunting #turkeyseason #learntohuntnyc

Scouted up a new spot with @snugthejoiner_aws this morning. Didn’t hear a thing from the roost so I started harvesting ramps, and then I heard a distant gobble and called two gobblers over in short order. They were hot and ready! Too bad for me it was youth day. Monday can’t come soon enough! #turkeyhunting #turkeyseason

Buzzer beater today! We were on some roosted birds who promptly followed hens out of reach onto private land right away, then nothing at all until we got a response at 11:25 am while sneaking around. 15 minutes later, we ended with a bang. On the board in Jersey! #turkeyhunting #learntohunt

I recently got a pellet smoker and it has been a game changer! I’ve always heard smoking is the best way to do turkey breast, and I’m completely sold. I’ve also been trying out the full suite of sauces and seasonings from @pure_whitetail and am really liking them. If you check them out, my code will get you 20% off the whole website. Huntingactor20
#purewhitetail #wildgamecooking

Look at this little guy! Is he not the most adorable thing? We bumped a doe from cover along a trail and stopped, and then this tiny fawn walked right up to us. Never seen anything like it. Seems like he didn’t realize we weren’t his mom at first. Eventually he decided to go hide and we left them alone to reunite.

The mushroom gods rewarded me for getting my exhausted butt out to the woods today!! A couple spots were surprisingly barren but overall it seems like a banner year for morels this year. Lots of dandy singles on poplar trees plus a couple nice groups around ash trees made for a solid day. #foraging #morels #learntohuntnyc
One year ago today, I drove @snugthejoiner_aws across the country from his birthplace to our home!

Nothing like tagging out before 6:30 am! Turkey season is such a grind out here on these public lands. Nice to finally have some more luck and put some poultry in the freezer. #savageambassador #savagerenegauge #wearesavage #learntohuntnyc

Had a solid day in the morel woods. Things are dry and warm out there so I think these will be about the last I find this year. We also found what I think is a tiny bear skull. What do y’all think it is?

Love the reaction! Never gets old helping someone learn to break clays for the first time! P.S. two long beards walked across the range while everyone was firing and were unfazed 🤣 #savage555 #wearesavage #savageambassador
Look what I found! August 1994, Knoxville News Sentinel. I started young!
Doing some steadiness work with @snugthejoiner_aws in the park today.

It’s mushroom time, baby!! First day back from Spain and we hit the woods for a quick hike. The woods are full of mushrooms and we picked a nice little basket of early Chanterelles and Lilac Boletes to cook with.
I wish I had the time and skill to make this food look as good as it tastes. Chanterelles and Bolete pizza with roast garlic and fresh basil and spinach. Collab with @mishajapanwala
I can never resist a good Old Man of the Woods portrait!
The humidity sucks, and the mosquitoes are maddening, but the woods are bursting with a cornucopia of fungi this year.  Bring on the rains!!
#solidarity #sagaftra #strike let’s go!

Despite having a favorite patch stripped by someone (they didn’t even leave buttons!) I had a banner day in the woods. Picked around 20lbs of Chanterelles, a few milk caps, and half a pound of trumpets.
Chicken of the woods are all over the place right now in NJ!

Never gets old teaching someone to break clays for the first time! Really enjoying having a 20ga over under for the job instead of a 12ga. Didn’t know what I was missing. Savage 555 is awesome. #savageambassador #wearesavage #learntohunt
Check this out! You can actually see the cloud of spores coming off these oyster mushrooms! Tough to get on camera. You could see it better in person, but look closely and you’ll spot them.

What a day! Probably my last chanterelles haul of the year with deer season coming in hot. And such fun to share the woods in harmony with such delightful people. Not many hunting outfitters with vegan clients but we’re closer to each other than we are to folks who aren’t putting thought and energy into where their food comes from. Bring on the cooking!

Dove season! The joy and anticipation of this tradition on 9/1 is something I have known since I was 5. I never missed one until I moved North to pursue an acting career. Sadly, NY and NJ both lack a season, so PA is the closest place I can go. It’s been years since I had a decent hunt as a result. I can’t wait to put these guys on the grill!!
#savage555
#savageambassador 
#wearesavage

Had a beautiful black bear cruise by me while deer hunting this afternoon in Morris County, NJ. He had an ear tag and looked to be about 300lbs by my estimation. Right in Central Park of Morris County!
Congrats to @thefeeshbeach on your first deer!
Very tempting but with three already in the freezer, she got a pass tonight.
Had the pleasure of teaching @brooklyntaxidermy to break clays today with the Savage 555! #savageambassador #wearesavage

It’s been a tough start for me with getting my clients their opportunities. I keep getting opportunities when I’m alone and then my clients get winded, or we blow deer out on our way in, or another hunter ruins our chances. Really nice to have one go exactly to plan for a change! This was his first hunt, and first deer. Many thanks to @theforagedfeast for getting me in the door at this awesome new spot. #learntohunt #plusonemovement #r3
Had a great Apprentice Hunt this afternoon! I love spoiling people on their first hunt if I can. This is number 6 for the season. #learntohuntnyc #deerhunting #firstdeer #plusonemovement

Bowhunting is so much harder than most people realize. That’s why I spend so much effort trying to convince my clients to start out with a crossbow. Can you tell what went wrong for this guy? #learntohunt #bowhunting #deerhunting

We got a second chance this afternoon and redemption was sweet! It’s generally not wise archery to shoot them quartering towards you like that but he put this one right on the money. #learntohunt #firstdeer #bowhunting

After a string of bad luck to start the season, we had a string of good luck this week! In six sits, we had deer in range 7 times, resulting in three harvests. Two were first time hunters, and this dandy was the well deserved payoff to my first successful client who passed on a pair of young bucks before the big guy came through. I love October! Gonna be a great month!!

Very tricky hunt this morning! The wind was basically dead, so even though this deer approached from what should have been a crosswind, she was still able to detect something wrong in the air. The client did an outstanding job of getting her in his sights without spooking her, even though she sees some movement in the tree. At that point it was now or never, and he made a perfect shot, squeezing the bolt just behind the shoulder bone due to her slightly quartering towards position. I screwed up the camera work and with the fog, it was impossible to assess the shot, so we gave it two hours before we tracked. The bolt was completely green with stomach contents and no blood, which made sense given the angle but was still concerning. Thankfully there was a big blood trail so we committed to tracking, and she was recovered easily. Very grateful for another harvest from the @weatherwool swamp. #firstdeer #deerhunting #learntohunt

“Wait for him to turn” is where I am starting this video for a reason. Earlier, as the deer was coming down the road, I felt the need to say “Wait for him to come close.” On the range during this client’s shooting lesson, my instructions had been consistently ignored. In the blind, I had to ask him not to rest his finger on the trigger multiple times. So I had reason to be worried about how this opportunity would play out. To my dismay, the client fired at a bad angle when he had no reason to rush. Thankfully, the power of the crossbow made up for his bad choice, blasting right through the shoulder blade with enough force to break the spine. I dropped the camera and immediately took the crossbow from him, readying it for a follow up shot, which turned out to be unnecessary. This deer expired quickly, but I have seen similar shots result in suffering. He wanted no part of field dressing his deer, and decided that it was too much meat and he didn’t want to keep it after all. While I’m always happy to add venison to my freezer, this is not how I want it to go down. On the ride home, he told me he wants to come again for a duck hunt in the winter. If you’ve read this far you probably know how likely he is to hunt with me again…

We had an outstanding and fast hunt this morning! Deer walked in on us before shooting time. I heard them coming so we’re able to hold still before they saw us getting situated in the stand. The old matriarch eventually figured out that something was off when she walked to the base of the tree, but she stopped quartering away at 20 yards to look back and the client made a perfect shot, only a few minutes past legal shooting time. We stayed put and 15 minutes later got the opportunity to double and I caught it on camera. Shot was a little back on the second one but it took out the liver and the deer didn’t suffer long. This cool weather is the best! #learntohunt #deerhunting #learntohuntnyc

My client did an awesome job on his first buck in the rain this morning. The wind was being very naughty and we had already been winded by an unseen deer coming from the same direction that this buck came from. I spotted him taking his time in the thick stuff, and let the shooter know. He seemed cautious, then calm, then moved calmly towards the exit. I had expected him to stop and feed, but he was looking to find a doe that wasn’t there. We had actually discussed this exact scenario earlier on, and the shooter was ready for it. I realized it was leaving, called the shot quartering away, and he didn’t make it 30 yards after the shot. Gotta love an early success on a gloomy day! #firstdeer #deerhunting #fueledbynature

Had a fantastic morning with @theforagedfeast and @snugthejoineraws chasing early season ducks! We had our Wood Duck limit in the first ten minutes and added two big ducks to the strap by the time it was over. Snug got in his some of his first proper duck retrieves, too! The weather, the leaves, and the water were all in rare form as well. Can’t wait to cook these tasty things. #savagearms #wearesavage #savageambassador #duckhunting #learntohunt

We had some incredible foraging over the weekend! Tons of Shrimp of the Woods, and the biggest individual Hen of the Woods I’ve ever found. Great fun with @mishajapanwala @snugthejoiner_aws and @natashajapanwala

Had another outstanding morning of duck hunting in the Swamp with @natureintoaction and @snugthejoiner_aws today! We again harvested our limit of Wood Ducks in less than 15 minutes, and spent the rest of the morning mostly watching them work in and land over and over again. Wish we could take more than three, but it was still a lot of fun to watch them! We did get surprised by a rare for here Pintail later in the morning to add to the bounty. Snug’s work was improved from Monday: he was able to retrieve everything for us! Now time to get back to deer hunting for a while. It’s almost that magical time! #duckhunting #learntohunt #savageambassador #savagearms #wearesavage

Ten minutes after I finished texting my staff guide that I was worried about having made the wrong choice for our hunt location today, this happened! Funny how quickly things can turn around. Last night we saw some great early rutting scans nearly got a big boy. The fall leaves are in peak form. It’s a fantastic time to be out here!! #learntohunt #deerhunting #learntohuntnyc

What a day! I was so stressed about whether we would see deer today, and we ended up having both clients take a buck. One in the morning, then this one in the afternoon. We had an awesome encounter with him, grunting and chasing in a small doe, then chasing off the big doe we thought we were going to take, before giving us an opportunity for the client to make a perfect shot. We had chasing last night as well. The game is getting hot out there! #deerhunting #publiclandowner #learntohunt #fueledbynature
Lion’s Mane are out now! Here’s what to look for. #foraging #learntohuntnyc #lionsmane

So close on a good one just now but he got our wind and backed out, just barely avoiding giving up a shot opportunity. Pretty surprised to see a big guy moving this early in the heat, but anything’s possible right now, clearly! #learntohunt #deerhunting #rut
The wind got the best of us up north, but down south our staff guide @adam_sennick put a hurting on them this morning with his client! Congrats guys.
I don’t love the taste of liver, but @snugthejoiner_aws is crazy about it. So whenever a client doesn’t keep it, I turn them into dog treats. #dogtreats #venison #learntohuntnyc

I’m so happy for this guy. I wanted to get him on a deer so badly! He’s been a bus driver and dispatcher for 30 years, and wanted to try out hunting as a way to stay active when he retires next summer. I took him to a spot that is usually a slam dunk yesterday and this morning, but the rut and heat has had the deer spending their time elsewhere. We moved spots in the afternoon, but he balked at the new tree stand, a soaking wet, 20 foot high hang on, so we had to go sit by a big tree with a little bit of cover and pray for it to work out. We first had a spike approach from behind us and then disappear just before we had a chance, likely due to the wind. An hour later this deer popped out of the roses at 15 yards with no warning!! He noticed the client frantically trying to get a shot off and took a few steps away, offering a steep quartering away shot at 20 yards. I heard the smack and saw him mule kick, but couldn’t see the hit. I thought I heard him crash close by. We found no blood at all, so we went in the direction of the crash, and he hadn’t made it 30 yards. The bolt entered very far back, preventing blood from escaping, but the bolt had gone through the center of the heart. A great finish for a great client and his very determined guide. #firstdeer #learntohunt #learntohuntnyc
null

Tagged my buck today! This one nearly got away. He always seemed to be there when I wasn’t, and when he came I nearly blew it. He came in right at the start of shooting time when it was still quite dark. I heard heavy footsteps and then grunting, then saw a big body and confirmed it was him once I could see the outline of his rack. He gave me a quality shot at 18 yards and buck fever somehow got the best of me. At the shot mule kicked and sprinted 80 yards downhill, stood for 10-15 seconds, then bolted off to the left. I listened for the crash but instead heard what sounded like him slowing down and walking. My guts turned. I waited an hour to get down and found gray, then white fur at the hit site. So definitely a low hit, exiting the belly fur. I was high above him so it might have been okay. The blood trail was immediate and profuse. Even though he was sprinting, there was tons of blood. I thought: no need to wait longer, this deer is long dead. I found a huge pool of blood where he stopped. But the blood just kept going for a bit too far, especially given my impression that he was walking when he was further down the trail. I found him bedded down, still alive, and had somehow managed to get within 40 yards and avoid spooking him. Luckier still, he was fairly upright and nearly broadside. I didn’t dare risk getting closer. I gave myself time to calm down and squeezed off a follow up shot that ended his suffering quickly. It was a great lesson for me to deal with some buck fever again, because I see it so much with clients. It’ll help me be a better guide for sure. Grateful to have filled my bow tag with such a big, old buck. Going to have a lot of great meals and memories from him.

We tagged another nice buck this morning! He snuck in super quiet at 9:15 and the client put a perfect shot on him at 15 yards. Grateful to @ironboundhardcider for the opportunity to help keep their deer herd manageable. #learntohunt #deerhunting

Short story for this one! We sat all morning watching birds and squirrels, then this buck snuck in and offered a money shot. We didn’t even have to track him! #deerhunting #learntohuntnyc #learntohunt

When in doubt, back out. Especially on a nice cool day. This morning we got a late start due to surprise tunnel closures but the deer were in the mood and it didn’t matter in the end! After maybe 30 minutes in the stand, this fine buck cruised past us at 25 yards. In the heat of the moment the client forgot that he could stop the deer and shot while the deer was moving without leading him. I saw the hit was too far back and the deer stopped after a short run, then very slowly walked out of view. We stayed on stand for almost four hours before getting down because I was worried he bedded close by. The more I thought about it the more I felt like we might have hit liver which should be fatal by then, and so we started the track. Tracking was easy while he was walking through cover but blood became scarce in the open woods. I decided to play it safe and called in a licensed dog tracker, who recommended we give it a bit longer in case the liver was missed. Stomach shots can take 8 hours to be fatal. In the end, the deer had only made it another 150 yards, and we found him dead in his first bed. Very happy we could recover this one, and lots of fun getting to see the dog work! That’s the 20th deer shot and recovered for myself and clients so far this season. #learntohunt #bowhunting #deerhunting

Tons of action today, especially in the morning. This little buck that we harvested has very recently been beaten up by a bigger one. His antler on one side is just ripped out! Ouch!! I didn’t get this one on camera but stay tuned for some good encounters incoming.

We hunted from the ground without a blind this morning because this spot just doesn’t have a place where you can hide with either when the leaves are down. We had hot action all morning, but it comes with the challenge of finding an open shot in thick spice bush. #learntohunt #deerhunting #learntohuntnyc

Today’s client was visiting from Alaska! Even as a resident, he’s still not been drawn for a big game tag in several years of living there, so he has made time to hunt with me in NJ. I took him to the absolute best place I could, and we had tons of action but awful wind in the morning. He passed the only fawn that was foolish enough to come into range, and stayed on stand all day hoping for a midday buck. At 4pm, the same herd that winded us in the morning started to tiptoe back through. The wind was still squirrely and they were all extremely cautious. She made the mistake of standing broadside at 40 yards and he made a perfect shot on her. I’m very hesitant about clients shooting that far with archery, but this guy has the experience and my crossbow is very accurate, so I didn’t object and it all worked out beautifully. This makes 22 harvested deer for myself and clients this season, plus five more that my staff have put people on. Hopefully we can keep it going!
Had a great morning in the @weatherwool swamp chasing ducks with a client, @snugthejoiner_aws, and my Savage Reneguage. #savageambassador #wearesavage

This guy is one of those people who’ve kept coming back and investing in hunts with me despite bad luck over a couple years. He just kept on catching the days when it didn’t happen.  Tonight I took him to the closest spot I have to a sure thing to try and break the cycle. The morning was windy and void of deer. As dark neared and the wind was blowing in a bad direction I was losing hope, but a doe appeared and thus began an intense encounter with multiple deer, finally ending in a double. I’m short the doe was smelling us and thinking about bolting when this Buck showed up and harassed her into a shooting lane for us. He didn’t understand what had happened when she took off, and ended up offering a ten yard shot. That makes 24 for the season. Hopefully will add one or two before Thanksgiving break! #firstdeer #bowhunting #plusonemovement #fueledbynature

My old reliables came through for me tonight. This spot is nearly always good at sunset for a public land doe during this second gun season. The client really wanted to bow hunt but I convinced him to let me bring the Savage along for backup. Wouldn’t you know it, she came from directly downwind and started stomping and snorted at us. No way she was coming to his range, so I put a slug through her heart. I was so twisted up trying to shoot to my weak side that the recoil knocked my hat off! Another great day filling folks’ freezers with venison. Extra fun that I got to be the trigger man this time. That’s number 29 the season. Two more chances to get to 30 before I go on my Christmas break! #savageambassador #wearesavage #savagearms #learntohuntnyc

Yesterday I was very lucky to be invited to hunt in Balochistan, Pakistan for the second time. I harvested this mature Chinkara Gazelle (they’re so little!) with a borrowed .270 and am looking forward to cooking with it for Christmas dinner! My last hunt was only my second day ever in Pakistan and it was difficult to process the experience. Everything was so overwhelming. This time it was much more familiar, and allowed me to enjoy the landscape and the people even more.

Got in some great Karachi monuments and sights checked off the list this year! Quaid-e-azam’s Mazar, Abdullah Shah Ghazi Shrine, and the Mangroves of Korangi Creek. Being a foreigner, I received special treatment at both tombs. We were given the opportunity to see the now closed to the public tomb chamber of Jinnah and watch the changing of the guards ritual. The acoustics of this space were absolutely spectacular, with powerful overtones ringing after the leader’s voice. In Korangi Creek we followed @khanaymeikyahai to hear the stories and enjoy the food of the local fisherfolk who are experiencing a lot of challenges in this time of climate change and industrial pollution. #karachi #pakistan
My first time as a guest and not the groom of a Pakistani wedding was great fun! Tossed into the mix here is the Chinkara gazelle leg which I cooked Hyderabad style for Christmas lunch. #roomforrabo

Ended 2023 with a surprise invite to help out with an old fashioned driven hunt followed by a walk around hunt to clean up. I think today was the best day of @snugthejoiner_aws life! What a great way to close out the year! #americanwaterspaniel

It’s a very bittersweet night for me. I had luck with a fat doe at sunset, but the reason why I am back to deer hunting for myself is a sad story. I came home from Karachi to discover that my main freezer was off. The breaker in the outlet had been tripped, and the entire contents of the freezer were between 53 and 56 f. It must have been off for days to get that warm in there. After much wringing of hands I concluded that I had to discard everything rather than risk illness. So tonight I dragged a heavy doe into my backyard, but I carried 145 lbs of venison, duck, pheasant, turkey, and salmon to the curb. It’s devastating, honestly, but at least I have a reason to do some deer hunting for myself, and time to fill the freezer before the season ends. #30

Broke out the smooth bore for some buckshot action today! Morning was slow but the afternoon was red hot. Could easily have been a three deer afternoon, but happy to come away with one and another first deer for a happy client. #learntohuntnyc #learntohunt #deerseason #31#savageambassador

The Savage was hungry in the cold today! It can be a real challenge to hunt in these conditions. It’s not just frozen extremities. Gear locks up. Deer can hunker down. The ground is crunchy and sound carries. But sometimes it’s awesome. Today we got rewarded with a beautiful landscape, a very full freezer, and another spoiled client taking a deer on his first hunt. I love working hard in the cold! #firstdeer #plusonemovement #savageambassador #savagearms #wearesavage #33 and #34

We had a great public land snow hunt today. It snowed all day. We got to see a fox running around barking for a mate and scouted a bunch of deer tracks. Set up at my favorite spot in the afternoon and had a group of ten deer descend from the mountain top. We hunted from the base of a tree on the ground and they didn’t notice us even at 40 yards. The client patiently waited for this large doe to offer a shot and put it right on the money.  Really pleased to be having this much success so late in the season! I’ve still got quite a few open weekdays available if you’d like to come out and give it a try. This is my 35th successful harvest of the year and another first deer on a client’s first hunt. #plusonemovement #firstdeer #learntohuntnyc #learntohunt #savageambassador #savagearms #wearesavage
